modules.description: Implements low-level event loop operations for handling file descriptors, timers, and signal notifications. Provides functions to register, update, and remove event sources, along with dispatching triggered events to callbacks. Designed for direct use in building custom event-driven applications like network servers and asynchronous I/O handlers.

Handles event-driven I/O operations with file descriptors, timers, and signals. Works directly with Unix file descriptors and custom callback handlers. Useful for implementing network servers and asynchronous I/O systems where precise event control is required.

This module implements a low-level event loop for handling I/O operations on file descriptors and timed events. It provides functions to register callbacks for readability and writability of file descriptors, schedule delayed actions, and manage the lifecycle of the event loop and associated resources. Concrete use cases include building network servers that handle multiple connections concurrently or implementing custom I/O multiplexing logic with precise timing control.
